# 🔱 LiTTree Lab Studios — CLINE RULES
# Read before executing ANY tool call or file modification.
# This file is consumed by the Cline VS Code extension.

[ENVIRONMENT]
- PLATFORM: Windows 11 (native, NOT WSL2).
- WORKSPACE_ROOT: C:\Users\litbi\CascadeProjects\litlabs\reference-repo
- SHELL: PowerShell 7 / Windows PowerShell. VS Code's workspace default is PowerShell.
- START_DIRECTORY: Always verify `Get-Location` is exactly
  `C:\Users\litbi\CascadeProjects\litlabs\reference-repo` before running project commands.
- RUNTIME: Next.js 16 (Turbopack Engine) | React 19 | Tailwind v4 | pnpm 9.15+
- NODE: 22+ (verified: v22.22.3, pnpm 9.15.9)

[PROJECT_TRUTH]
- This is a multi-agent AI app: LiTTree Lab Studios.
- Real subsystems (all verified to exist on disk):
    src/lib/litt.ts            — LiTT notification dispatcher (exports the legacy `jarvis` singleton for compatibility)
    src/lib/litt-context.ts    — LiTT brain / prompt builder / action helpers
    src/lib/AgentOrchestrator.ts — orchestration matrix
    src/lib/agent-logger.ts, agent-profiles.ts, agent-tools.ts,
    agent-validation.ts, agent-worker.ts, agentCommands.ts, agent-user.ts
    src/lib/director-graph.ts   — director agent graph
    src/lib/supabase.ts, supabase-admin.ts, supabase-client.ts
    src/lib/llm.ts, llm-completion.ts, llm-executor.ts
    src/lib/auth.ts, jwt.ts
    src/lib/r2.ts               — Cloudflare R2 storage
    src/lib/usage.ts            — usage telemetry
    src/lib/TaskRepository.ts   — task persistence
- There is NO src/lib/jarvis.ts. The `jarvis` export is defined in `src/lib/litt.ts` for compatibility.
- Repository (git remote): https://github.com/LabsConnected/litlabs-website
- Branch: main
- Deployed on Vercel. Self-host via Dockerfile or docker-compose.yml.

[CRITICAL_RULES]
1. NEVER assume the workspace is empty or "minimal". If a file is missing, your context is
   wrong — read the file or run `dir` / `Get-ChildItem` first.
2. NEVER scaffold default Next.js / Tailwind / create-next-app boilerplate. The project is mature.
3. NEVER downgrade Next.js, React, or Turbopack.
4. NEVER introduce `~`, `$HOME`, `/mnt/c`, or any Linux path. The host is Windows.
5. NEVER edit `.env.local`, `.env*.local`, `.env.vercel-*`, or `.sb_anon_key`. They contain secrets
   and are git-ignored for a reason.
6. NEVER use `keytar` directly — it requires native compilation. It is a transitive dep only.
7. The Devin config is `.devin-config.json` (root-level). The legacy `devin.config.json` is
   kept for backward compatibility — if asked to update Devin, update BOTH files.
8. `lucide-react` is pinned to `^1.24.0` (very old, pre-rename). Many modern icons are
   unavailable — prefer inline SVG (see `src/components/dashboard/AutonomicLoopBanner.tsx`) or
   `src/components/dashboard/AutonomicLoopBanner.tsx` for the pattern.
9. Use PowerShell syntax only. Never use `head`, `tail`, `grep`, `findstr`, `if exist`, `2>nul`,
   `%ERRORLEVEL%`, `&&`, or Unix shell redirection. Do not mix cmd.exe, bash, and PowerShell.
10. Do not run `cd C:\Users\litbi\CascadeProjects\litlab`; that is a different sibling checkout.
    If the current directory is wrong, use
    `Set-Location -LiteralPath 'C:\Users\litbi\CascadeProjects\litlabs\reference-repo'`.
11. Before editing, read the exact current file region. Use Cline's native file-edit tool with a
    complete valid edit block. If an edit fails, re-read the file before retrying; never guess at
    stale context.
12. If a follow-up-question tool errors, continue with the safest reasonable interpretation when
    the user already authorized the task. Do not loop on the broken question tool.

[COMMANDS]
- Dev server: `pnpm dev` (Turbopack on :3000) or `pnpm dev:webpack` as a fallback.
- Build: `pnpm build`
- Lint: `pnpm lint`
- Test: `pnpm test` (Vitest + jsdom)
- Type-check: `npx tsc --noEmit`
- Terminal server: `pnpm terminal:dev` (separate process on its own port).

[POWERSHELL_PATTERNS]
- Show first lines: `Get-Content -LiteralPath <path> | Select-Object -First 80`
- Show last lines: `Get-Content -LiteralPath <path> -Tail 80`
- Search text: `rg -n '<pattern>' <path>`
- Check a path: `Test-Path -LiteralPath <path>`
- Remove a temporary file: `Remove-Item -LiteralPath <path> -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue`
- Capture output and exit code: run the command normally; use `$LASTEXITCODE` only if needed.
- Run commands sequentially as separate tool calls. Do not chain unrelated commands.
- Prefer project binaries when launchers are broken: `.\node_modules\.bin\tsc.cmd --noEmit` and
  `.\node_modules\.bin\eslint.cmd <paths>`.

[QUIRKS]
- `cleanDistDir: false` in next.config.ts to avoid Windows EPERM errors on `.next/` cleanup.
- `serverExternalPackages: ["jose"]` to fix the middleware NFT build error.
- Turbopack `root: __dirname` suppresses a lockfile-detection warning on Windows.
- `ignore-scripts=true` in `.npmrc` — postinstall scripts are skipped; install native deps manually.
- Supabase migrations live in `supabase/migrations/`; never write to `supabase/schema.sql`
  directly — it is regenerated by `supabase db pull`.
- Route groups: `(auth)` is a non-URL segment.
- `tsconfig.json` has `strict: true` — type errors are real. Always run `npx tsc --noEmit`
  before claiming a change is "done".
- `litlabs/`, `litlabs-website/`, `Zoo-Code/`, `work/`, `meta/`, `chrome/`, `codex-reference/`
  are large local artifacts and are excluded from `tsconfig.json`. Don't import from them.

[DEPLOYMENT]
- Vercel: `git push origin main` triggers CI via `.github/workflows/build.yml` and Lighthouse via `.github/workflows/lighthouse.yml`.
- Docker: `docker build -t litlab .` (or use `docker/Dockerfile.terminal` for the terminal server).
- Heavy studio work (`/studio`, image generation) should run on GitHub Codespaces, not locally.
